reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy build, perfect fit
reviews.reviewText: I finally purchased a legit cabinet after having the plastic Target container in my bathroom. I don’t know why it took me so long because this piece was so affordable and it looks so cute in the bathroom. It took me about 2 hours to build alone but it was pretty easy. It’s not as heavy as it looks but it’s still good quality. It didn’t have any missing parts, they actually send a few extra screws just in case AND as a bonus, it comes with a screwdriver. Plenty of storage, and the shelves of different heights help accommodate all the bathroom amenities.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the money
reviews.reviewText: The product was just what I was looking for. Easy to assemble, great color, after fixed at the wall it’s pretty sturdy. All the parts were in the box, fitted perfectly the space I had for it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Don’t let the bad reviews scare you
reviews.reviewText: I never write reviews but I thought I should make an exception for this - I was worried about putting this together because I’m a not mechanically inclined and I read that some people had trouble. I really agonized over whether I should get it, especially since the shipping was twenty bucks. But I’m happy to say, it’s totally worth the price, even with the shipping. I just laid everything out, identified all the pieces and little packets of hardware, which were labeled (sometimes I had to look a bit to find the little sticker) and followed the directions. It was a little tricky in some places so you really HAVE look at the directions closely. If you do that, it comes together relatively easily. I didn’t have any trouble with holes not lining up. I only made one mistake by putting one of the shelves upside down so you can see the little screws but I didn’t bother to fix it because I would have had to take it all apart again. You can’t see it unless there is nothing on the shelf and the door is open anyway. I did it ALL BY MYSELF except for having my 78 year old mother hold the doors so I could screw in the hinges. It took me about 3 hours- a far cry from the 30 minutes for 2 people it said, and my hand hurt from all the screwing, but I was very proud of myself and happy with the product. It is quite sturdy. And once I secured it to the wall, it wasn’t tippy at all. It has made a huge improvement in the look of my bathroom.As far as smell- if you have chemical sensitivities, you should probably give this and other furniture like this a pass. It does have an odor that isn’t pleasant but it’s not super strong to me and I expect it will fade with time.The one thing that I don’t love is the drawer, which doesn’t pull out too far, making it a bit difficult to reach into the back but that is a minor concern.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: All pieces felt strong and of good quality. Instructions were well written, steps easy to follow. I built it by myself and it took me about 2.5 hours. The only part that was difficult by myself was attaching the doors, but the Instructions recommend a two person team. This is very sturdy and I had ample extra screws by the end of the build. I was very impressed that the kit came with its very own screw driver! And one of good quality as well. I'm very impressed with this product and the company. 5 stars! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟
